<CSSLength>
<summary>
The <strong><c>&amp;lt;length&amp;gt;</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Types">data type</see> represents a distance value. Lengths can be used in numerous CSS properties, such as <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/width">width</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/height">height</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/margin">margin</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding">padding</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-width">border-width</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size">font-size</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/text-shadow">text-shadow</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><para><strong>Note:</strong> Although {{cssxref(&amp;quot;&amp;lt;percentage&amp;gt;&amp;quot;)}} values are usable in some of the same properties that accept <c>&amp;lt;length&amp;gt;</c> values, they are not themselves <c>&amp;lt;length&amp;gt;</c> values. See {{cssxref(&amp;quot;&amp;lt;length-percentage&amp;gt;&amp;quot;)}}.</para></blockquote>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/Building_blocks/Values_and_units">CSS values &amp; units tutorial</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Values_and_Units">CSS values &amp; units reference</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model">Box Model</see><br/></para>
